                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C1112/97: Telegram (part air)</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-02-01T10:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 1, 1937—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 2—12:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>54. Consulate’s 38, January 26, 7 p.m. The Secretariat is issuing invitations for
                    the Raw Materials Committee to meet at Geneva, March 8. Grady will be notified
                    direct.</p>
                <p>The Secretary General has addressed a communication to the German Government
                    asking if it desired to suggest an expert to be appointed a member of the
                    Committee. The Italian Government is being addressed in somewhat similar
                    terms.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
